BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:A Streetcar Named Desire
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20270326T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20270326T213000
DTSTAMP:20260712T153920Z
UID:occ-1293@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:Tennessee Williams' 1947 tragedy of Blanche DuBois\, her illus
 ions\, and the brother-in-law who sees through them.\n\nTennessee Williams
 ' 1947 drama\, still one of the towering American plays. After losing the 
 family home to creditors\, Blanche DuBois arrives in a cramped New Orleans
  apartment to live with her sister Stella and a brother-in-law\, Stanley K
 owalski\, who has no patience for her airs or her illusions. A flicker of 
 hope appears in Stanley's courtly friend Mitch\, but Blanche's past keeps 
 circling closer. From Arcadia Theater\, Alpharetta's community company.
GEO:34.0765277;-84.2884766
LAST-MODIFIED:20260712T153742Z
LOCATION:Arcadia Theater\, 180 Academy St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
